Source: gitls
Section: vcs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Sven Siepermann <sven@siepermann.dev>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), libgit2-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.0
Homepage: https://github.com/sven42xyz/gitools
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: gitls
Architecture: any
Depends: libgit2-1.7 | libgit2-1.1 | libgit2-1.3 | libgit2 (>= 1.0), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: A fast, minimal tool to inspect and act on multiple git repositories
 gitls recursively scans a directory for git repositories and displays
 their status in a compact table: branch name, staged/modified/untracked
 file counts, ahead/behind remote, and relative last-commit time.
 It also supports bulk branch switching with the -s flag.
